## Notifications

### Notification Types (exhaustive list — do not add new types without    updating this list)  -- should be updated
| Type | Trigger | Target |
|------|---------|--------|
| `article_pending` | Author submits article | All Reviewers |
| `article_approved` | Reviewer approves | Article author |
| `article_rejected` | Reviewer rejects | Article author |
| `new_comment` | User comments on article | Article author |

> Note: `new_comment` notification is triggered by CommentService (Lahiru's domain).
> Lahiru must call `notificationService.send()` from within `CommentService.addComment()`.
> The `NotificationService.send()` method is **Chathurika's** to implement and own.

```typescript
// src/services/notification.service.ts
export class NotificationService {
  async send(payload: NotificationPayload): Promise<void> {
    await notificationRepository.create({
      userId: payload.userId,
      type: payload.type,
      title: payload.title,
      referenceType: payload.referenceType,
      message: payload.message,
      referenceId: payload.referenceId,
      readStatus: false,
    });
  }

  async sendToRole(role: UserRole, payload: Omit<NotificationPayload, 'userId'>): Promise<void> {
    const users = await userRepository.findByRole(role);
    await Promise.all(
      users.map(user => this.send({ ...payload, userId: user.id }))
    );
  }

  async markRead(notificationId: string, userId: string): Promise<void> {
    const notification = await notificationRepository.findById(notificationId);
    if (notification?.userId !== userId) throw new AppError('Not authorized', 403);
    await notificationRepository.updateReadStatus(notificationId, true);
  }

  async getUnreadCount(userId: string): Promise<number> {
    return notificationRepository.countUnread(userId);
  }
}
```

