## Tech Talk Management

### Status Machine
```
[Draft] ──publish──→ [Published]
   ↑
   └─── (Admin edits) ──→ [Draft]  (editing resets to Draft automatically)
```

### Business Rules
- Only **Admin** can create, edit, publish, republish, or delete Tech Talks
- Editing a Published Tech Talk automatically resets status to `Draft`
- Republish = explicit action to re-publish after editing (POST /republish endpoint)
- Delete requires confirmation pop-up (handled on frontend)
- Soft delete: set `deleted_at` timestamp, do not hard delete
- Published Tech Talks: sorted by `event_date DESC` by default
- Supports: title search, date sort, title sort

```typescript
// src/services/tech-talk.service.ts
async update(id: string, updates: TechTalkUpdateInput, adminId: string): Promise<TechTalk> {
  const existing = await techTalkRepository.findById(id);
  if (!existing) throw new AppError('Tech Talk not found', 404);

  // Editing always resets to Draft
  return techTalkRepository.update(id, {
    ...updates,
    status: 'Draft',    // always reset on edit
    updatedAt: new Date(),
  });
}

async publish(id: string): Promise<TechTalk> {
  const talk = await techTalkRepository.findById(id);
  if (!talk) throw new AppError('Tech Talk not found', 404);
  if (talk.status === 'Published') throw new AppError('Already published', 400);
  return techTalkRepository.updateStatus(id, 'Published');
}
```

### Tech Talk Fields
```typescript
interface TechTalk {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  presenters: string[];        // array of presenter names
  tags: string[];
  eventDate: Date;
  slidesUrl: string | null;    // optional link/download URL
  youtubeUrl: string | null;   // YouTube embed iframe URL
  status: 'Draft' | 'Published';
  createdBy: string;           // Admin user ID
  deletedAt: Date | null;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
}
